## 9. Risk Factors

- **Industry-specific risks:** Demolition is cyclical and tied to commercial construction activity; fuel and subcontracted-labor inflation has been compressing contractor margins industry-wide. Asbestos/hazardous-material exposure on interior gut-outs carries regulatory and liability risk.
- **Financial risks:** No multi-year financials disclosed — the 3-year growth trend cannot be verified. The "cash flow" figure is an SDE/discretionary-earnings proxy, not an add-back-verified EBITDA; actual normalized EBITDA after a market owner's wage may be lower. Project revenue creates working-capital swings.
- **Operational risks:** Customer concentration is undisclosed (largest segment ≈30%); a single large GC or municipal account could be material. Safety performance and OSHA/EMR history must be verified given the demolition trade.
- **Regulatory / legal:** OSHA demolition standards, Colorado/Denver demolition permitting, asbestos abatement licensing (AHERA/state), and landfill-diversion requirements. Confirm all licenses transfer and EMR is clean.
- **Deal-specific conditions:**
  - **Negotiate price from 5.48x to ≤4.0x cash flow (≈$2.57M) as a condition of the deal.**
  - Obtain 2024 + 2025 (and ideally 2022–2023) P&L and balance sheet to confirm the 3-year growth requirement before advancing.
  - Confirm whether cash flow is true EBITDA or SDE, and re-cast with a market-rate replacement wage for the owner.
  - Verify the founding date (SOS filing) to confirm the years-in-business assumption.

